      "intent_thread_url": "https://groups.google.com/a/chromium.org/d/msgid/blink-dev/69a779c1.050a0220.1426e8.0068.GAE%40google.com",
      "announcement_url": null,
      "experiment_goals": "Origin Trial's goal was to gain insights on websites' usage of Connection Allowlist header and receive feedback from developers on whether there are any updates that would be useful.\n\nAs was mentioned in the I2E, at the start of OT, the following network endpoints were implemented: \nSubresources fetch, Navigations, Redirects, fetches from local scheme navigations (via connection allowlists inherited from the navigation's initiator), history.back/forward navigations, rel=prefetch, rel=preconnect, rel=preload, rel=modulepreload, , rel=dns-prefetch, and their link header equivalents.\n\nAs OT progressed, support was added for remaining known network endpoints including webRTC, WebTransport, WebSocket and others. Connection allowlists support documents, dedicated workers, shared workers and service workers.\n\n\n",
      "experiment_risks": "Since this is a defense in depth measure and also because we are continuing to add more network endpoints mitigation as the OT continues, it is strongly recommended that websites use this in conjunction with their current security mechanisms including content security policy. Since this feature increases the data exfiltration protections of a site, if this experiment comes to an end, the site will lose those mitigations. Continuing to use their existing security measures will ensure those sites will be back to their current security level if the experiment ended.",
      "origin_trial_id": "2487675844168777729",
